5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 320, L.D. 491, “Resolve, Authorizing
10 the Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry to Convey and Release the
11 State's Interest in Certain Real Property Located in the Town of Richmond”
12 Amend the resolve by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, Requiring the Director of the Bureau of Parks and Lands to Convey Certain
14 Real Property in the Town of Richmond'
15 Amend the resolve by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
16 'Preamble. The Constitution of Maine, Article IX, Section 23 requires that real estate
17 held by the State for conservation or recreation purposes may not be reduced or its uses
18 substantially altered except on the vote of 2/3 of all members elected to each House; and
19 Whereas, certain real estate authorized for conveyance by this resolve is under the
20 designations described in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 12, section 598-A; and
21 Whereas, the Director of the Bureau of Parks and Lands within the Department of
22 Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry may sell, lease or exchange lands with the approval
23 of the Legislature in accordance with the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 12, sections 1814,
24 1837 and 1851; now, therefore, be it
25 Sec. 1. Director of Bureau of Parks and Lands directed to convey certain
26 land in Town of Richmond. Resolved: That, notwithstanding any provision of law to
27 the contrary, the Director of the Bureau of Parks and Lands within the Department of
28 Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry shall by quitclaim deed and without covenant
29 convey the State's interest in property described in section 2 to Wilhelmine Dennis Oakes
30 or the estate of Wilhelmine Dennis Oakes. Any legal or closing costs of the conveyance
31 may not be paid by the bureau.
32 Sec. 2. Property interests to be conveyed. Resolved: That the property required
33 to be conveyed pursuant to section 1 is a parcel of land of approximately 7 acres with
34 improvements thereon, located in the Town of Richmond and shown as Lot 67 on Map R6
35 of the Town of Richmond tax assessor maps.'
